        "text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Meave London began with a problem its founder, Meave Sinclair, could not stop thinking about. As an interior stylist in London, she spent her days making rooms feel calm and finished, only to watch them undone by one thing: harsh, badly placed lighting. The pieces she loved needed an electrician, a wall chase and a budget most of her clients did not have.</p><p>During a long winter at home, she started sketching a different kind of light: a wall sconce with the warmth and proportions of a designer piece, but completely wireless. No drilling, no rewiring, no permission from a landlord. The first brass prototype went up in her own hallway in 2021. Within weeks, friends and clients were asking where they could buy one.</p><p>So she made more. Today Meave London designs warm, wireless wall lights, shades and furniture accents for people who want a styled, finished home without the renovation.</p>",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_font": "body",
            "secondary_color": false,
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
